    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your<strong> slow cooker</strong> to high</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> diced chicken </strong>and the<strong> onion petals </strong>to the pan and cook for 5-6 min, turning halfway, or until golden</p><p>Once golden, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the contents of your pan to the <strong>slow cooker </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until everything is coated in the flour</p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[255ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>dried thyme </strong>(save the remaining dried thyme for another recipe!) and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Gently stir it all together, cover and cook on high for 3 hours or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chicken stew </strong>has been cooking 3 hours, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle and return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, then season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander with your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and pour <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> all over or until the spinach has wilted and the peas are warmed through</p><p>Stir your <strong>soft cheese</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>through the <strong>chicken stew </strong>until combined \u2013 this is your <strong>slow cooker creamy chicken stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-creamy-chicken-stew-with-mash-and-greens/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>slow cooker creamy chicken stew</strong> with the <strong>mash </strong>and <strong>greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the <strong>greens</strong> with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season everything with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
